    "path": "src/agent/session",
    "name": "session",
    "purpose": "Owns the agent session runtime and session preview context. session.rs defines Session startup, worker routing, package_message(SessionEvent) -> SessionMessage, and route_session_event; after a host channel connects, spawn_host_worker resets SessionState.context and sends an ExecutionEvent::PreviewQuery so the host can return tool previews, and route_session_event stores ExecutionEvent::Preview tools into SessionState.context while still safely ignoring standalone Step events because StepEvent carries no TaskSignature or TaskId. session_state.rs defines SessionState storage for task queues, shared client/host endpoints, and a StdMutex<SessionContext> initialized with empty task and tool lists. session_context.rs defines SessionContext, which holds task previews and tool previews only. mod.rs is namespace and re-export wiring only.",
